    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf I open a file and add extra newlines at the end of it and then write to the file and quit `:wq`, then when I re-open the file _one of the newlines is gone_. If I repeatedly re-open the file and exit with `:wq`, then one of the newlines will disappear each time a exit the file until there are no trailing newlines left.\r\n\r\nI'm pretty sure this shouldn't happen?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\r\necho -e \"{ 1 : 2 }\\n\\n\" > dank.json\r\nnvim --clean dank.json  # notice the two trailing newlines. now exit with :wq\r\nnvim --clean dank.json  # notice there is only ONE trailing newline. now exit with :wq\r\nnvim --clean dank.json  # notice there are NO trailing newlines left. now exit with :wq\r\nnvim --clean dank.json  # now the file is unchanged since last exit\r\nnvim --clean dank.json  # still unchanged\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ntrailing newlines should not be removed _automatically_\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim --clean DOES NOT behave the same (vim 9.0)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n13.4.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew",
