            "body": "ðŸ¤¦ yup, there's a `.editorconfig` file in the directory in question. I didn't even know that was a thing.\r\n\r\nin that case, maybe neovim is not interpreting the `.editorconfig` `insert_final_newline=false` correctly.\r\n\r\nI don't think it should remove newlines if they exist - it should just not add one if it's not already there.\r\n\r\nI tested this behavior in a folder without the `.editorconfig` and misbehavior was gone",
